      "side": 1,
      "message": "So your specific devices are programmed to provide hwmon sensors? What about ones that aren\u0027t? \n\n[ANS] it is a CPLD device which defined registers to control Fan device via pwm/tacho ports. BMC read/write those registers to control Fan. \"BMC \u003c-i2c-\u003e CPLD \u003c-\u003e Fans\"\n \nHow can there be a hwmon driver in the kernel for an FPGA that is guaranteed to work if someone isn\u0027t using your image?\n\n[ANS] If user implement this kernel driver and CPLD is located on i2c-XX/0xXX, he/she can guarantee to work by manual command in their BMC console\n\n1. echo lcmx03lf 0xXX \u003e /sys/bus/i2c/devices/i2c-XX/new_device\n2. ls -l /sys/bus/i2c/devices/XX-00XX\n3. cat /sys/bus/i2c/devices/XX-00XX/hwmon/hwmon*/fan1_input   # tach\n4. cat /sys/bus/i2c/devices/XX-00XX/hwmon/hwmon*/pwm1",
      "parentUuid": "cac42d6f_d08f3bce",
